<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-37-0489 </DOCNO><TEXT>The invention concerns a plant for heat recovery and for the simultaneousutilisation of air and solar energy in connection with a building. Theplant has a first heat exchanger, which is connected to a solar plantand/or absorbs part of the heat to be recovered from the building andemits it to the outside air flowing through. A second heat exchangeris supplied with the heated air and supplies heat to a subsequent heatload. (orig./BWI).</TEXT></DOC>